Robust Regression

Lieven Clement

statOmics, Ghent University (https://statomics.github.io)

1 Robust regression in R

1.1 Simulate 20 observations from a linear model with errors that follow a normal distribution

set.seed <- 112358
nobs <- 20
sdy <- 1
x <- seq(0, 1, length = nobs)
y <- 10 + 5*x + rnorm(nobs, sd = sdy)

1.2 add outlier at high leverage point

y[nobs] <- 7

##fit linear model

ols <- lm(y ~ x)

##fit robust linear model

library(MASS)
mEst <- rlm(y ~ x)

##plot results

plot(x, y)
abline(ols, lwd = 2)
abline(mEst, col = "red", lwd = 2)
legend("topleft",
  legend = c("OLS", "M-estimation"),
  lwd = 2,
  col = 1:2)

round(mEst$w,3)
##  [1] 0.885 1.000 1.000 1.000 1.000 0.840 1.000 1.000 1.000 1.000 1.000 1.000
## [13] 1.000 1.000 1.000 1.000 1.000 1.000 1.000 0.233

2 Implement it yourself

2.1 start from ols fit

lmMod <- ols

2.2 Use robust variance estimator to calculate the z

res <- lmMod$res
stdev <- mad(res)
median(abs(res-median(res)))*1.4826
## [1] 1.595375
z <- res/stdev

2.3 calculate weights

2.4 use psi.huber function

w <- psi.huber(z)
plot(x, y)

plot(x, lmMod$res)

plot(x, lmMod$res, cex = w)

3 perform a weighted regression use lm with weights=w

lmMod <- lm(y~x, weights = w)

4 plot results

plot(x, y)
abline(ols, lwd = 2)
abline(mEst, col = "red", lwd = 2)
abline(lmMod, col = "blue", lwd = 2)
legend("topleft",
  legend = c("OLS","M-estimation","Our Impl"),
  lwd = 2,
  col = c("black", "red", "blue"))

5 repeat this many times

lmMod <- ols
for (k in 1:10)
{
######repeat this part several times until convergence
#use robust variance estimator to calculate the z
res <- lmMod$res
stdev <- mad(res)
median(abs(res-median(res)))*1.4826

z <- res/stdev

#calculate weights
#use psi.huber function
w <- psi.huber(z)

#perform a weighted regression use lm with weights=w
lmMod <- lm(y ~ x, weights = w)

#plot results
plot(x,y)
abline(ols, lwd = 2)
abline(mEst, col = "red", lwd = 2)
abline(lmMod, col = "blue", lwd = 2)
legend("topleft",
  legend = c("OLS","M-estimation","Our Impl"),
  lwd = 2,
  col = c("black", "red", "blue")
  )
####################################
}
